<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Marine Dies After Nighttime Hike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CAMP LEJEUNE, N.C. (AP) -- A 21-year-old Marine lance corporal  
died at Camp Lejeune after a night hike early Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Guiseppe Leto of New Milford, Conn., was a student at the School  
of Infantry at the Marine base. 
</P>
<P>
	The cause of death was under investigation, officials said.  
</P>
<P>
	Leto, assigned to the Infantry Training Battalion, had completed  
the hike when he lost consciousness. Efforts to revive him at the 
scene failed, according to Camp Lejeune officials. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
