<HEADLINE> Packers Sign Mike McKenzie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- The Green Bay Packers have signed  
cornerback Mike McKenzie, who was a third-round pick in last 
April's draft, the team said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	McKenzie will report to training camp with other rookies July  
25, general manager Ron Wolf said. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot, 190-pound McKenzie was a cornerback and safety at  
Memphis. The Miami native finished his three-year college career 
with 206 tackles, six interceptions and 28 stops on other teams. 
</P>
<P>
	The Packers have signed four of its 12 selections from the 1999  
draft. 
  	   	
