<DOCNO> APW19990708.0026 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-08 16:30:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ump Hallion Suspension Rescheduled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- National League umpire Tom Hallion will serve  
his three-game suspension from July 19-21 rather than this weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	The NL announced the suspension on July 2, saying Hallion was  
disciplined for his actions during an argument with Colorado 
catcher Jeff Reed and pitching coach Milt May. 
</P>
<P>
	With the second half of interleague play starting Friday, 10 NL  
teams are home, which means 40 umpires are needed. 
  	   	
