<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boy Convicted of Murdering Neighbor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BARTOW, Fla. (AP) -- A teen-ager was found guilty Thursday of  
fatally bludgeoning and stabbing his 8-year-old neighbor and then 
stuffing her body into the frame of his waterbed. 
</P>
<P>
	A jury convicted 15-year-old Joshua Phillips of first-degree  
murder in the death of Maddie Clifton, who lived across the street 
from him in a Jacksonville neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
	The defense had urged jurors to convict the boy of manslaughter,  
saying the killing was not premeditated. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're not here to act out of some form of vengeance,'' defense  
attorney Richard Nichols told jurors. ``We're not here to act as a 
bunch of well-dressed vigilantes.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Joshua showed no emotion as the verdict was read. Maddie's  
parents, Steve and Sheila Clifton, blinked back tears. 
</P>
<P>
	Maddie disappeared Nov. 3, 1998, prompting a search of her  
Jacksonville neighborhood involving hundreds of volunteers. Her 
decomposing body was found seven days later stuffed in the frame of 
Joshua's water bed across the street from her home. 
</P>
<P>
	Joshua's attorney argued that the Maddie's murder wasn't  
premeditated and urged jurors to convict him of manslaughter. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're not here to act out of some form of vengeance,'' defense  
attorney Richard Nichols told jurors. ``We're not here to act as a 
bunch of well-dressed vigilantes.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But in his closing argument Thursday, the prosecutor, State  
Attorney Harry Shorstein, said Phillips ``made a conscious 
decision'' to kill Maddie. ``That's premeditated murder.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Detectives testified during the trial that Joshua confessed to  
the murder. 
</P>
<P>
	According to Joshua's story, he accidentally hit Maddie in the  
eye with a baseball while they were playing in his backyard. She 
began screaming, and he panicked, dragged the girl into his 
bedroom, where he hit her with a bat and then stabbed her. 
</P>
<P>
	``The evidence shows us there was an accident that deteriorated  
into panic and then murder,'' Nichols said. 
</P>
<P>
	But Shorstein said Joshua's story was unlikely and suggested  
that the murder may have been sexually motivated. There was no 
blood on the ball, no blood in the yard and no dirt on Maddie's 
body or clothes. An autopsy showed Maddie was beaten over the head 
and stabbed at least 11 times in the chest and neck. 
</P>
<P>
	Joshua, who was 14 at the time, was tried as an adult. Since he  
is under 16, he cannot be sentenced to death in Florida. He could 
be sent to prison for life with no chance of parole. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
