<HEADLINE> Sting Beat Rockers 75-62 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- The Charlotte Sting combined a  
record-setting 3-point performance by Dawn Staley with dominating 
work on the boards to overpower the lowly Cleveland Rockers 75-62 
on Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Staley hit a club-record five of her six 3-point attempts and  
wound up with 22 points and five assists, leading the Sting to 
their fourth victory in six games. 
</P>
<P>
	Charlotte, which made a franchise-record nine of 13 3-pointers,  
also got 13 points and eight rebounds from Vicky Bullett and seven 
boards apiece from Charlotte Smith and Andrea Stinson. 
</P>
<P>
	The Sting (5-5) had a 34-19 rebounding advantage over a  
Cleveland team that came in with a WNBA-worst record of 2-10 and a 
league-low scoring average of 64 points. The Rockers' rebound total 
was the lowest this season for a Charlotte opponent. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rockers, who never led, lost their fourth game in a row and  
fell to 0-7 on the road. 
</P>
<P>
	Eva Nemcova had 11 points and Janice Braxton 10 for the Rockers,  
who completed a four-game road trip in which they were outscored by 
a combined 42 points. 
</P>
<P>
	In addition to their inside problems, the Rockers lost point  
guard Suzie McConnell Serio to foul trouble just past the midway 
stage of the first half. Cleveland turned it over six times the 
rest of the half, clearing the way for the Sting to go up by as 
many as 10 on the way to a 31-24 halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
	Staley hit four 3-pointers to help Charlotte stretch its lead to  
13 less than nine minutes into the second half. The Sting's biggest 
lead was 17 in the closing minutes. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
