<HEADLINE> Silverbulletday Returns To Fillies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OCEANPORT, N.J. (AP) -- Silverbulletday, seventh in the Belmont  
Stakes June 5 in her debut against males, will return to 
competition against 3-year-old fillies Saturday at Monmouth Park -- 
and they're not exactly rushing to welcome her back. 
</P>
<P>
	Mike Pegram's winner of 11 of 13 starts drew only four rivals  
for the 1 1-16-mile Monmouth Breeders' Cup Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
	Silverbulletday, the odds-one favorite, will start from the  
outside post, which shouldn't matter. 
</P>
<P>
	``Five's good,'' trainer Bob Baffert said Thursday by telephone  
from California. ``Out there she can break and do things her way. 
You don't worry to much about a five-horse field, anything less may 
be different.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``I'd hate to be coming out of the one hole,'' Baffert said.  
``Down there you can get pinned in, but outside she'll have a clear 
break.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Silverbulletday galloped over the Monmouth track Thursday  
morning in her first real exercise since arriving Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
	``She just loved the track,'' said Peter Hutton, a Baffert  
assistant. ``She galloped about a mile and a half this morning and 
was really going well. Her ears were pricked, and she was taking it 
all in stride. I couldn't pull her up. She's happy, has settled in 
nicely, and seems to really like the track.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Silverbulletday, who will be ridden by Jerry Bailey, had her  
final serious work for the Oaks on Monday at Churchill Downs, 
breezing six furlongs in 1:11 2/5. 
</P>
<P>
	Completing the field for the $250,000 Oaks are Bag Lady, Aaron  
Gryder; West's Secret, no rider; Chatter Patter, no rider, and Boom 
Town Girl. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
