<HEADLINE> Corn, Soybeans Up; Wheat Mixed / Board of Trade  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Corn and soybean futures prices advanced early  
today on the Chicago Board of Trade, while wheat futures were 
mixed. 
</P>
<P>
	Corn and soybeans moved higher as investors continued to  
consolidate positions following sharp losses earlier this week. 
Prices were expected to face continued pressure, however, from 
forecasts for near-ideal Midwestern growing weather over the next 
10 days. 
</P>
<P>
	Wheat futures were mixed, pressured by harvesting of the winter  
wheat crop, but supported by reports of increased export demand. 
</P>
<P>
	Wheat for December delivery was unchanged at $2.65 3/4 a bushel;  
December corn rose 1 1/4 cents to $2.05 1/2 a bushel; December oats rose 
1 1/2 cents to $1.10 1/2 a bushel; November soybeans rose 1/2 cent to $4.23 
a bushel. 
</P>
<P>
	Live cattle futures were mixed, while feeder cattle futures  
retreated on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. Pork futures advanced 
strongly. 
</P>
<P>
	August live cattle fell .42 cent to 62.45 cents a pound; August  
feeder cattle fell .65 cent to 76.70 cents a pound; August lean 
hogs rose 1.18 cents to 45.75 cents a pound; August pork bellies 
rose 3.58 cents to 39.30 cents a pound. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
