<HEADLINE> European Stocks Mixed; Trading Dull </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
        LONDON (AP) -- Bank shares were in the spotlight in European  
trading Thursday, an otherwise lackluster day of thin trading. 
</P>
<P>
        Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index was up 0.3 percent. In London,  
the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was down 0.6 percent. 
Milan's MIBtel index was flat; Madrid's IBEX-35 index was down 0.9 
percent and the French CAC-40 index was down 0.7 percent. 
</P>
<P>
        Copenhagen had the best day with a 1 percent gain in the KFX  
index. 
</P>
<P>
        The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 594 European companies closed  
down 3.99 points, or 1.2 percent, at 319.43, while the Dow Jones Euro 
Stoxx Index, which tracks 295 companies in countries that joined the 
euro single currency, finished up 0.30 points at 335.37. 
</P>
<P>
        The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index ended up 0.51 points at 3951.  
00, while the DJ Stoxx 50 Index was down 7.56 points at 3894.12. 
</P>
<P>
        German bank shares were higher after Deutsche Bank upgraded  
Dresdner Bank and Bayersiche HypoVereinsbank and recommended buying 
local bank shares. 
</P>
<P>
        Dresdner finished 6.2 percent higher and Hypo was up 0.8 percent.  
Deutsche Bank gained 4.8 percent and Commerzbank was up 3.9 percent. 
  	   	
</P>
