<HEADLINE> Greg Norman Gets Golf Clubs Back </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JUPITER ISLAND, Fla. (AP) -- A man charged with stealing two sets  
of clubs from golfer Greg Norman returned them when he realized 
they were ones Norman uses in tournaments. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't think he knew at the time he'd stolen THE tournament  
clubs of Greg Norman,'' explained police Officer Bill Smith. 
</P>
<P>
	Once he realized that, he ``panicked and brought them back,''  
Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
	James Jankowski, 22, was arrested Wednesday night and charged  
with grand theft and violation of probation for swiping the 
custom-made Cobra clubs from Norman's garage Saturday. Police said 
Jankowski had done work on Norman's roof about a week earlier. 
</P>
<P>
	The clubs were returned to Norman before he left Tuesday for  
Scotland to prepare for the British Open, Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
	Norman said he was ``very pleased to get my tournament clubs  
back.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Jankowski remained behind bars Thursday without bond.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
