<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> June, Year to Date Retail Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	June sales and sales for the fiscal year to date reported by  
leading retailers. 
</P>
<P>
	The sales compare the current year's sales with those of the  
previous year. Retailers are ranked according to results at the end 
of June. 
</P>
<P>
	Reporting periods vary slightly. Most retailers' fiscal years  
end in late January or early February. 
</P>
<P>
	Sales include those from stores open at least a year, also known  
as same-store or comparable store sales, and total sales. Retailers 
release only percentage changes for same-store sales, while they 
provide dollar figures and percentages for total sales. 
</P>
<P>
	Securities analysts and investors believe same-store sales  
provide a more accurate assessment of a retailer's performance than 
total sales. 

</P>
<P>
 *Wal-Mart Stores Inc.  
</P>
<P>
 *Five weeks ended July 2: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 6.5 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $14.87 billion, up 13.6 percent from $13.09  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Five months ended July 2: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 8.1 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $62.30 billion, up 15.1 percent from $54.15  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Kmart Corp.	
</P>
<P>
 *Five weeks ended June 30: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 9.2 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $3.51 billion, up 11.3 percent from $3.16  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Five months ended June 30: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 6.6 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $14.4 billion, up 8.5 percent from $13.27  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Sears, Roebuck and Co.	
</P>
<P>
 *Five weeks ended July 3: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 1.9 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $3.76 billion, down 3 percent from $3.88  
billion. 
</P>
<P>
 *Five months ended July 3: 
</P>
<P>
	Same-store sales rose 1.2 percent.  
</P>
<P>
	Total sales were $16.12 billion, down 3.1 percent from $16.64  
billion. 
</P>
