<HEADLINE> Illiquidity Wins Belmont Feature </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Illiquidity survived a steward's inquiry and  
gained a neck victory in the $43,000 turf feature for mares 3 and 
older at Belmont Park Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Eze finished second in the 10-horse field. It was another 3 3/4  
lengths to Forever Cindy. 
</P>
<P>
	Illiquidity bore out nearing the wire but was deemed not to have  
interfered with Eze. 
</P>
<P>
	Illiquidity, who raced coupled in the wagering with Hedge Ratio,  
carried 116 pounds with John Velazquez over one mile in 1:34. She 
earned $25,800 for Klaravich Stables with her second win in five 
starts this year. 
</P>
<P>
	The winning entry returned $6.10, $3 and $2.50. Eze paid $3.20  
and $2.80 and Forever Cindy was $9.50 to show. 
  	   	
