<HEADLINE> NL All-Stars Add Reds' Williamson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Rookie right-hander Scott Williamson of the  
Cincinnati Reds was selected Thursday to replace injured Robb Nen 
of the San Francisco Giants on the National League All-Star team. 
</P>
<P>
	Williamson is the third Reds' representative, joining starting  
shortstop Barry Larkin and first baseman Sean Casey.. 
</P>
<P>
	Williamson is 7-3 with 10 saves and a 1.55 ERA in 58 innings.  
His wins and saves top all National League rookie pitchers. His 23 
2-3 consecutive scoreless innings from April 30-June 11 is the 
longest streak in the majors this season. 
</P>
<P>
	The All-Star game will be Tuesday night at Boston.  
</P>
