<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Airborne Freight, down 1 5/16 at 25 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The express delivery company said it will report second-quarter  
earnings between 45 cents a share and 55 cents a share. Analysts 
have called for 62 cents per share. Airborne Freight cited light 
domestic shipments. 

</P>
<P>
 *Consolidated Stores Corp., down 6 7/8 at 16 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	Consolidated, a retailer specializing in closeout merchandise,  
expects a loss of 2 cents a share in the second quarter, due in 
part to slow video-game sales. Analysts estimated the company would 
earn 6 cents a share. 

</P>
<P>
 *Apria Healthcare Group, up 1 7/8 at 18 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Apria said Thursday the U.S. Attorney's office in Sacramento,  
Calif., has closed its criminal investigation of the company's 
billing practices for Medicare and other patients in federal health 
care programs. 

</P>
<P>
 *Mylan Laboratories, down 1 5/8 at 28 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	A federal judge has refused to dismiss the federal government's  
antitrust lawsuit against Mylan, a maker of generic drugs. The 
Federal Trade Commission seeks at least $120 million for refunds to 
customers. 

</P>
<P>
 *Loews Cineplex, down 7/8 at 10    	
</P>
<P>
	Loews widened its losses in its fiscal first quarter, to 37  
cents per share compared with 3 cents per share in last year's 
first quarter. The company blamed poor box-office results, 
particularly compared to last year, when the blockbuster film 
``Titanic'' was in theaters. 

</P>
