Apple, saying the company's stock should hit 75 in the next 12 
months. 

</P>
<P>
 *MCI WorldCom Inc., up 4 13/16 at 90    	
</P>
<P>
	Salomon Smith Barney included MCI WorldCom in its list of 15  
stocks believed to be attractive investments for the coming year. 

</P>
<P>
 *Bradlees Inc., up 2 13/16 at 17 13/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Sales at established stores for the discount retailer rose 24.8  
percent in June. In the year to date, Bradlees said these sales 
rose 15.6 percent, while total sales increased 14.2 percent. 

</P>
<P>
 *ACT Teleconferencing Inc., up 8 at 2 1/4    	
</P>
<P>
	ACT signed a three-year agreement to provide enhanced  
teleconferencing services to GTE Communications Corp. and its 
customers. ACT said the deal should significantly increase its 
annual revenue. 

</P>
<P>
 *Gymboree Corp., down 2 47/64 at 6 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	As sales stumble, Gymboree expects to report a second-quarter  
loss between 20 cents and 25 cents a share. In addition, the 
company will take a charge of 35 cents per share to update stores 
and products. Analysts had expected a loss of 2 cents per share. 


  	   	
</P>
