<HEADLINE> Amtrak Train Hits Truck, 4 Hurt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAGLE LAKE, Texas (AP) -- An Amtrak train hit a truck Thursday,  
derailing eight cars and injuring at least four people, none 
seriously. 
</P>
<P>
	The train, believed to be carrying 150 people, derailed 60 miles  
west of Houston about 11:45 a.m., said Mark Davis, a spokesman for 
Union Pacific Railroad, which owns the rail line. 
</P>
<P>
	Witnesses said the train hit a waste disposal truck at a  
crossing. 
</P>
<P>
	None of the injuries appeared serious, said David Keith,  
administrator of Rice Medical Center in Eagle Lake, seven miles 
west of the accident site. 
</P>
<P>
	The Sunset Limited was eastbound. It goes from Los Angeles to  
Fort Lauderdale, Fla. 
  	   	
