<HEADLINE> Mercury Coach Sidelined by Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- Phoenix Mercury coach Cheryl Miller had surgery  
Wednesday to repair her right Achilles tendon, partially torn while 
she was demonstrating a defensive move during practice. 
</P>
<P>
	Team physician Richard Emerson performed the operation and  
released Miller, who also is the team's general manager, to 
recuperate at home. 
</P>
<P>
	The 35-year-old Miller, one of only 11 women in the Basketball  
Hall of Fame, collapsed minutes into the team's practice Tuesday. 
It was the Mercury's first workout since a seven-game road trip 
ended Saturday at Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	She was told to sit out the home game Wednesday night against  
the Los Angeles Sparks, but was expected to return to the bench 
Friday night for a game with the Houston Comets. 
</P>
<P>
	Assistant coaches Linda Graf and Howie Landa were assigned  
coaching responsibility against the Sparks. 
  	   	
