<HEADLINE> Mets Farm Out Dotel, Recall Kinkade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Mets sent right-hander Octavio  
Dotel to Triple-A Norfolk and recalled infielder Mike Kinkade on 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	Dotel, who was 1-1 with a 6.61 ERA in three starts with the  
Mets, is expected to have a short-lived stay in the minors. 
</P>
<P>
	``Octavio is not being optioned to Norfolk as a result of his  
performance on the major league level,'' Mets general manager Steve 
Phillips said. ``With the All-Star break next week, we felt that he 
should make another start instead of having an extended period of 
rest.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Dotel is scheduled to pitch against Richmond on Monday for  
Norfolk, where he was 5-2 with a 3.99 ERA in 12 starts. He will 
start for the Mets at Baltimore July 19. 
</P>
<P>
	Kinkade started the season with the Mets and was hitting .196  
with two homers and six RBIs before his demotion to Norfolk May 22. 
  	   	
</P>
