<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-08 13:30:15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gucci Approves Alliance With PPR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AMSTERDAM, Netherlands (AP) -- Shareholders of Gucci Group NV on  
Thursday overwhelmingly approved the Italian fashion house's 
alliance with the French retail group Pinault-Printemps-Redoute SA. 
</P>
<P>
	At Gucci's annual meeting, shareholders gave the alliance their  
blessing by approving the nomination of four new PPR-affiliated 
members to Gucci's board and expanding the board to nine from eight 
members. 
</P>
<P>
	PPR acquired a 42 percent stake in Gucci in March.  
</P>
<P>
	``We see overwhelming support shown by our independent  
shareholders for our strategic alliance'' with PPR, said Gucci 
chief executive Domenico De Sole after the meeting. 
</P>
<P>
	The four new members sponsored by PPR are led by Francois  
Pinault, who controls PPR, and Serge Weinberg, the French 
retailer's chief executive. 
</P>
<P>
	Weinberg said he expects ``we're going to move forward'' with  
Gucci and PPR's agreed strategy to turn Gucci into a multi-brand 
luxury goods and fashion group through an aggressive acquisition 
strategy. 
</P>
<P>
	As expected, LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA -- which  
currently owns nearly 20 percent of Gucci's outstanding equity -- 
lambasted the approval of the alliance with PPR. 
</P>
<P>
	James Lieber, an LVMH vice president, called the vote ``a  
transfer of control to PPR, which is not in the interest of 
shareholders.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``We will proceed with our legal actions, which have a real  
chance of success,'' Lieber said, reiterating that LVMH intended to 
keep a stake in Gucci for the long haul. 
</P>
<P>
	The first step in the process of turning Gucci from a one-brand  
company into a multi-brand group is expected to be the acquisition 
of Sanofi Beaute, which owns rights to the prestigious Yves Saint 
Laurent brand. 
</P>
<P>
	Francois Pinault's Artemis investment arm acquired Sanofi Beaute  
from drug company Sanofi SA in March. Sanofi has since merged with 
Synthelabo SA to form Sanofi-Synthelabo SA. 
</P>
<P>
	At the same time, PPR invested $2.9 billion in Gucci in exchange  
for its 42 percent stake. Pinault's plan from the start was for 
Artemis to eventually sell Sanofi Beaute to Gucci. 
</P>
<P>
	Gucci chairman Andrian Bellamy told the shareholders' meeting  
that Gucci was under no obligation to purchase Sanofi Beaute. The 
four PPR-sponsored members on Gucci's board won't have any input in 
that decision, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	De Sole said Gucci was still auditing Sanofi Beaute's books and  
wouldn't decide whether to buy the company until that process was 
complete, possibly in September. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
