<HEADLINE> Headlines Headlines Headlines ..... </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 *New Mexico governor endorses Forbes for president    	
</P>
<P>
	SANTA FE, N.M. (AP) -- Gov. Gary Johnson endorsed Steve Forbes  
for the 2000 Republican presidential nomination Thursday, 
describing him through a spokeswoman as ``the man with the ideas.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Republican governor said, however, he will support whoever  
wins the party's nomination, according to his spokeswoman, Diane 
Kinderwater. 
</P>
<P>
	Both Forbes and Texas Gov. George W. Bush, the GOP front-runner,  
supported Johnson in his re-election campaign last year. Johnson 
has been Bush's guest at the Governor's Mansion in Austin. 
</P>
<P>
	``Should George Bush win the nomination, he will work hard to  
support him for the presidency,'' Kinderwater said. She said 
Johnson wrote to Bush about his decision to endorse Forbes. 
</P>
<P>
	``He feels strongly about the fact that Steve Forbes takes the  
high road and he talks about the issues,'' Kinderwater said. ``He's 
the man with the ideas.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson was not available for comment Thursday, the spokeswoman  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Welcoming the endorsement, Forbes praised the Republican  
governor for promising to halt new tax increases and to streamline 
New Mexico's state government. 
</P>
<P>
	Forbes came to Albuquerque last July and was the featured  
speaker at two fund-raising events for Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
	At the time, Johnson's campaign spokesman Doug Turner said the  
two were ``like-minded philosophically in that people do better in 
an environment with less-intrusive government.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
