<HEADLINE> Irvan To Drive for MB2 Through 2000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MOORESVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Ernie Irvan's contract to drive for MB2  
Motorsports has been extended through the 2000 Winston Cup season. 
</P>
<P>
	Irvan joined the team last year and has won three poles and  
posted 16 top-10 finishes. He is 22nd in the 1999 driver standings 
heading into Sunday's event in Loudon, N.H. 
</P>
<P>
	``Good things are going to keep happening for this race team,''  
Irvan, who has 15 career victories but none since 1997, said 
Thursday. ``I'm not finished winning, and I really believe I can 
get to Victory Lane with this team.'' 
</P>
<P>
	MB2 Motorsports, owned by Read Morton, Nelson Bowers and Tom  
Beard, became a full-time Winston Cup team in 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Irvan was on the verge of giving the team a top-10 finish in  
last year's points standings before late-season injuries in 
Talladega, Ala., sidelined him for the stretch run. He wound up 
19th. 
</P>
<P>
	``This team is still relatively young in that we've only been  
together for three years and have seen significant accomplishments 
in that time,'' general manager Jay Frye said. ``Ernie Irvan is one 
of the best drivers in the sport. Right now we have one of the best 
situations in Winston Cup racing.'' 
  	   	
