<HEADLINE> Accomplice Wins at Hollywood Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Accomplice charged through an opening  
on the rail turning for home and beat Ora Pro Nobis by 
three-quarters of a length to win Thursday's $52,400 feature at 
Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Corey Nakatani, Australian-bred Accomplice covered 5 1/2  
furlongs on the turf in 1:01 4-5 and paid $2.80, $2.20 and $2.10. 
The 6-year-old gelding won for the second time in three races since 
coming to the United States late last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Argentine-bred Ora Pro Nobis returned $3.40 and $2.10, while  
Argentine-bred Crows, making his first U.S. start, was another 4 1/2 
lengths back in third and paid $2.20 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory, worth $31,440, increased Accomplice's career  
earnings to $621,681, with nine wins in 20 races. 
  	   	
