<HEADLINE> Theo Fleury Signs With Rangers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Six-time All-Star Theo Fleury signed today with  
the New York Rangers as an unrestricted free agent. 
</P>
<P>
	The NHL club did not disclose terms of the deal, although  
Newsday reported he will receive $8 million for three years. 
</P>
<P>
	The 31-year-old Fleury played 11 years with the Calgary Flames  
before being traded to the Colorado Avalanche on Feb. 28. 
</P>
<P>
	He had 93 points on 40 goals and 53 assists during the 1998-99  
regular season. In the playoffs, he scored five goals and 12 
assists in 18 games for the Avalanche. 
</P>
<P>
	The 5-foot-6, 180-pound wing was a six-time NHL all-star and was  
a key member of Calgary's 1988-89 Stanley Cup championship club. 
  	   	
</P>
