<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Stocks End Mixed; Dow Down 60.47  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices were mixed today as strength in  
Internet and computer shares helped the technology sector 
outperform the broader market. At the close of trading on Wall 
Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was down 60.47 at 
11,126.89. The blue-chip index fluctuated between negative and 
positive territory for much of the session. Broader stock 
indicators were mixed. The Nasdaq composite index rose to a new 
record, while the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was off slightly. The 
Nasdaq rose 21.48 to 2,764.52. Nasdaq's strength came from a wide 
array of technology shares, including Yahoo! and Computer maker 
Apple. 

</P>
