have dumped stainless steel products in the United States. Nippon 
Steel Corp., which often acts on behalf of the nation's steel 
industry, called the decision ``extremely regrettable.'' In its 
final ruling, issued today, the ITC found that stainless steel 
imports from Japan and seven other nations had substantially hurt 
the U.S. steel industry. An official of Japan's Ministry of 
International Trade and Industry said the ministry will fully 
assess the contents of the ruling papers as to whether the ITC's 
judgment was appropriate. 

